   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <p>
      <seg rend="decorInit">M</seg>Eeting with many
Crosses in the world,
among them all I
found some in books,
as Crossing of Pro<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>uerbs,
Crosse answers
and such other like Crosse humours, as
I haue collected out of Crosse Authors,
which I haue here put together in this
little booke, in which, if you find any
thing crosse to your liking, crosse it out:
and if there bee any thing that is bet<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ter
worth then nothing, be not crosse
to patience to esteeme of a little, though
<pb facs="3"/>
but a little: so loth to crosse mine owne
Reason, with too much persswasion
of your too kinde, either dispo<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>sition
or discretion, I
rest as I finde
cause.</p>
   <closer>
      <signed>Your well-wisher,
<hi>B, N.</hi>
      </signed>
   </closer>
